WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified body profile for the RED V-RAPTOR camera. It contains the
exact mathematical IDT (Input Device Transform), Log3G10 curve parameters
with their inverse, native color space primaries, white balance presets,
ISO sensitivity ranges, and sensor metrology data. This is the single
source of truth for linearizing V-RAPTOR footage to scene-referred
ACES2065-1.

WHY IT EXISTS
RED’s IPP2 pipeline uses the REDWideGamutRGB (RWG) color space and
Log3G10 encoding. To integrate V-RAPTOR footage into an ACES or GIOP
pipeline, every pixel must be exactly linearized. Without this certified
body file, compositing, VFX, and grading workflows must rely on
proprietary SDKs or unofficial LUTs, introducing potential color errors.
This file provides the mathematically auditable IDT, eliminating the
black-box LUT.

HOW IT WORKS
The file defines the transform chain:
  1. Inverse Log3G10 (using the certified constants) → linear RWG RGB.
  2. RWG to ACES2065-1 matrix (3x3 certified).
  3. White balance scaling (as-shot or preset).
  4. ISO calibration and sensor gain model.
All constants are provided for the sensor’s native characteristics.

